{{DISPLAYTITLE:Elevator_LowerToNearest}} {{Special|247|tag, speed|Floor and Ceiling}} * ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How fast the elevator moves
Lowers the floor and ceiling of the tagged sector so that its floor aligns with the floor of the next lower sector while keeping the same amount of distance between the floor and ceiling.
== Examples == {{noexamples}}
== Conversions from linedef types == The following Doom map format types can be converted as Elevator_LowerToNearest: {| {{prettytable}} !Type!!Conversion!!Trigger |- |{{icon|Boom}} 231:W1 Elevator To Lower Floor || Elevator_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Cross |- |{{icon|Boom}} 232:WR Elevator To Lower Floor || Elevator_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Cross, Repeatable |- |{{icon|Boom}} 233:S1 Elevator To Lower Floor || Elevator_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Use |- |{{icon|Boom}} 234:SR Elevator To Lower Floor || Elevator_LowerToNearest (tag, {{xlat|ELEVATORSPEED}}) || Player Use, Repeatable |}
